Preliminary Wrangling¶

This dataset contains data from Bike sharing service Bay Wheels fromerly known as Ford Go Bike. Data used for exploration can be found at https://s3.amazonaws.com/baywheels-data/index.html .

#Merge all the 2019 months data files into a single master file for year 2019

file_name = 'baywheels_tripdata_2019.csv'
if not os.path.isfile(file_name):
    multi = []
    folder_name = 'Data'
    for cs in glob.glob(os.path.join(folder_name, '*tripdata.csv')):
        multi.append(pd.read_csv(cs))
    single = pd.concat(multi, ignore_index = True)
    single.to_csv(file_name, index = False, sort=True)
#single.head()

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset has total of 2506983 entries and 15 columns(features) with information like user id, bike id, location co-ordinates, name, start time , end time of the trip, rental method etc.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The intersting features will be : 

- The duration of the trip. <br>
- User types.<br>
- Time when the trip was taken(day of the week).<br>

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

Following features will be most helpful for my investigation :
duration_sec, user_type, start_time, end_time

Before starting our exploration lets look into our data and see how we can use it for our investigation¶

the data that we have downloaded from bucket has two names forgobike and baywheels as former name was rebranded into Bay wheels after April 2019. Lets look into what has changed in data during that period.

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

So from above we can say that. major userbase of the bay wheels service are subscibed to them(80%). Around 95% of the rides are of time less than half hour. Most travels are during the weekdays mostly for the comuting to work.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

I wanted data by month and day basis so I added those columns and removed the columns 'bike_share_for_all_trip','rental_access_method' as data for those features is not present for entire 2019 year. Also I droped the row with max duration seconds as there was only 1 record with rental duration of 10 days and others were very small compared to that around 10-20 mins. So I considered that record as outlier for our explorartion.
